Sure, here are some examples of sentences in Serbian that use the word "nadu" in different forms and positions, along with translations in English:

1. *Nadu* gubiš kad odustaneš prebrzo. (You lose *hope* when you give up too quickly.)
2. Ona je bila *naduta* jer je mislila da zna sve najbolje. (She was *arrogant* because she thought she knew everything best.)
3. Čim je videla mali *naduvani* balon, počela je da se smeje. (As soon as she saw the small *inflated* balloon, she started to laugh.)
4. Kada god se oseća *beznađe*, ona se seti svoje porodice i prijatelja. (Whenever she feels *hopelessness*, she thinks of her family and friends.)
5. Što više vazduha staviš u gumu, to će biti više *naduvana*. (The more air you put into the tire, the more *inflated* it will be.)
6. Neki ljudi smatraju da je *naduvan* balon simbol dece i detinjstva. (Some people consider an *inflated* balloon a symbol of children and childhood.)
7. Čak i u najtežim situacijama, ona ne gubi *nadu*. (Even in the toughest situations, she does not lose *hope*.)
8. Kada su svi bili *naduvani* od hrane, niko nije mogao da se pomera. (When everyone was *stuffed* with food, no one could move.)
9. Nije dobro biti *nadut* i umišljati da si najbolji, jer uvek postoji neko bolji od tebe. (It's not good to be *conceited* and think you're the best because there is always someone better than you.)
10. Posle celodnevnog planinarenja, bili su *naduti* od umora. (After a whole day of hiking, they were *exhausted*.)

I hope these examples help!